ls in any order and earn a “point” for each control you find. The only limitation is time: how many controls can you find before the clock runs out? Keep an eye on your watch, or else you’ll lose points for every minute that you’re late!\nWhile the terrain is rugged and navigationally challenging, the format of a score-o is beginner-friendly since you control (pun intended) the difficulty of every control simply by choosing which to find. And, if you have trouble finding a control, you can skip it and move on!\n“Greetings Orienteers- welcome to the upcoming doubleheader at Cle Elum. Bring water if desired and certainly a whistle with you. Safety bearing is S.E to the paved road. Lick Creek is a great area for orienteering. The map is slotted for further mapping so some overgrown vegetation in light or medium green may appear a bit thicker or expanded. Big thanks for contributions by Jourdan, Celia, and Alex Frank in vetting, computer work, and analysis. Enjoy the woods!” -Kean\n\nUltimate Series #7 (Score-O) – Lick Creek","external_links":[{"link_url":"https://goo.gl/maps/B2jdJ9eDWvJ2","link_type":"directions"},{"link_url":"https://goo.gl/maps/D6Xz52cRnUB2","link_type":"directions"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/event/ultimate-orienteer-7-score-o/","link_type":"event_page"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/map/lick-creek/","link_type":"map"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/result/ultimate-orienteer-6-classic/","link_type":"related_result"},{"link_url":"http://rg.cascadeoc.org/rg2/#144","link_type":"routegadget"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/series/ultimate-orienteer/","link_type":"series"},{"link_url":"http://cascadeoc.org/result/ultimate-series-7-score-o/#splits","link_type":"splits"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/season/ultimate-season-standings-16/","link_type":"standings"}],"volunteer_roles":[{"role_name":"Course Designer","individual_id":"019b7acf-182c-705a-a8fe-e71bcacc38a6","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Kean Williams","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Epunch Coordinator","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d2f-7807-bdc6-77a7e939a3ae","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Eric Jones","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Meet Director","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d2f-736d-863f-5e546e61e969","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Ing Uhlin","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"Web Snapshot: https://modern.cascadeoc.org/result/ultimate-series-7-score-o/","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"Ultimate Series #6 (Classic) – Teanaway Forks\nCheck back for Ultimate-O season points, all scores below reflect score-O event points.\nOpen 60 Minutes 30 C 1600 Pts 1:00:00\n\nSpecial parking information: Only cars with at least 4 people will be allowed to park in the lot. More information at the bottom of the page.\nMay 10th update: There will be NO participant parking at the Lick Creek gate. We are providing a shuttle to transport everyone to and from the registration/check-in area. See schedule and details at the bottom of the page.\nThe Ultimate Orienteer series is the sampler pack of orienteering: each event gives you the opportunity to try a different flavor!\nThe seventh event in the series is: SCORE-O!\nAt a score-o, you can find controls in any order and earn a “point” for each control you find. The only limitation is time: how many controls can you find before the clock runs out? Keep an eye on your watch, or else you’ll lose points for every minute that you’re late!\nWhile the terrain is rugged and navigationally challenging, the format of a score-o is beginner-friendly since you control (pun intended) the difficulty of every control simply by choosing which to find. And, if you have trouble finding a control, you can skip it and move on!\n“Greetings Orienteers- welcome to the upcoming doubleheader at Cle Elum. Bring water if desired and certainly a whistle with you. Safety bearing is S.E to the paved road. Lick Creek is a great area for orienteering. The map is slotted for further mapping so some overgrown vegetation in light or medium green may appear a bit thicker or expanded. Big thanks for contributions by Jourdan, Celia, and Alex Frank in vetting, computer work, and analysis. Enjoy the woods!” -Kean\n\nUltimate Series #7 (Score-O) – Lick Creek"}
